mythtv (0.20-svn20070609-0.1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Home for mythtv user is now /var/lib/mythtv (Thanks Michael Stella).
  * Removed mythtv-reconfigure-required.update-notifier script and
    dependency, because update-notifier depends on GNOME and is useless for
    headless machine.
  * mythtv-database recommends mysql-server.

 -- Christian Marillat <marillat@debian.org>  Wed, 13 Jun 2007 11:34:38 +0200

mythtv (0.20-svn20070609-0.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * New svn release. Last change is 13611.
  * Updated xmlt-tv grabber list.
  * Changes from Mario Limonciello (Ubuntu):
    o Updated text in mythtv-backend.templates, mythtv-common.templates and
      mythtv-reconfigure-required.update-notifier to better reflect current
      packages workings of the user mythtv.
    o New patch 06_alsa_default to make alsa the default handler rather than
      oss.
    o New patch 07_backend_crash_without_tuner to prevent random backend
      crashes when no tuner was present.
    o Moved the "exit 0" to the correct place in mythtv-database.postinst
    o Unset two env variables in mythtv-backend.init to get rid of ominous
      warnings when starting the backend in X.
    o Added a space after echo -n "Starting $DESC: $NAME " and echo -n
      "Restarting $DESC: $NAME " in mythtv-backend.init
    o Added update-notifier to mythtv-database depends.

 -- Christian Marillat <marillat@debian.org>  Sat, 09 Jun 2007 16:43:59 +0200

